[1
Date: 5 Mar 2001
From: Prof. Dr. G.A. Balint <BALINT@nepsy.szote.u-szeged.hu>

Taking into consideration the FMD epidemics in Europe, Hungary has also
introduced, with the effective date of 4 Mar 2001, some measures at the
borders:
1. Ban on animals entering Hungary, particularly when the addressee is in
Croatia, because Croatia closed down her borders completely from this point
of view.
2. Compulsory disinfection of all vehicles at the Hungarian border.
3. Compulsory disinfection of all aircraft which arrive in Budapest
(Ferihegy) airport from an infected country. This measure includes the
destruction (incineration) of all waste and garbage from such aircraft. The
disinfection of the passengers' shoes has not yet been introduced, but if
the situation worsens it will be introduced.
No FMD case or suspected case has been detected at the present moment in
Hungary.
--
Prof. G.A. Balint
Univ.of Szeged Medical School
Hungary
<BALINT@nepsy.szote.u-szeged.hu>
