[2
Date: 5 Mar 2001
From: Pig Disease Information Centre <pdic@btinternet.com>
Source: News Agency [edited

The Belgian ministry of agriculture announced this afternoon that all
limitations implemented this weekend are withdrawn, with the following
exceptions:
The buffer zone around the farm is now 10 km (was 20). Within this zone all
the limitations are still in force.
For the rest of Belgium, 2 measurements [restrictions are still in force:
1. Every farm with even-toed animals must have a container available to
disinfect the feet of visitors.
2. Only essential access of persons and vehicles is permitted to farms.
--
Pig Disease Information Centre
<pdic@btinternet.com>
